{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"storeBytes","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"of","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"value","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv10storeBytes2of12toByteOffset2asyx_Sixmts15BitwiseCopyableRzlF1TL_xmfp"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"toByteOffset","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"offset","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":" = 0, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"as","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"type","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv10storeBytes2of12toByteOffset2asyx_Sixmts15BitwiseCopyableRzlF1TL_xmfp"},{"text":".Type) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"BitwiseCopyable","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/BitwiseCopyable","preciseIdentifier":"s:s15BitwiseCopyableP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The value to store as raw bytes."}]}],"name":"value"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset from this pointer, in bytes. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offset"},{"type":"text","text":" must be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"nonnegative. The default is zero."}]}],"name":"offset"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"type"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":" to be stored must be a trivial type. The memory","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"must also be uninitialized, initialized to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":", or initialized to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"another trivial type that is layout compatible with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"After calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)"},{"text":", the memory is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initialized to the raw bytes of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":". If the memory is bound to a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"U"},{"text":" that is layout compatible with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":", then it contains a value of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"U"},{"text":". Calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)"},{"text":" does not change the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bound type of the memory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A trivial type can be copied with just a bit-for-bit copy without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any indirection or reference-counting operations. Generally, native"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift types that do not contain strong or weak references or other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"forms of indirection are trivial, as are imported C structs and enums."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to store into memory a copy of a value of a type that isn’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trivial, you cannot use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Instead, you must know either initialize the memory or,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you know the memory was already bound to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type"},{"text":", assign to the memory.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, to replace a value stored in a raw pointer ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"U"},{"text":" is the current type and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":" is the new type, use a typed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pointer to access and deinitialize the current value before initializing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the memory with a new value:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let typedPointer = p.bindMemory(to: U.self, capacity: 1)","typedPointer.deinitialize(count: 1)","p.initializeMemory(as: T.self, repeating: newValue, count: 1)"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/UnsafeMutableRawPointer\/storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)-3chnc","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"8.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated